HOMPAGE: http://www.mikekohn.net/
PURPOSE: Helps in the creation of ringtones

-------------------------------------------------------------------

NOTE:  For most up to date docs please read: 
       http://ringtonetools.mikekohn.net/

       I don't always update this file very well

-------------------------------------------------------------------

THIS MAY NOT BE USED IN COMMERCIAL ENVIRONMENTS WITHOUT
PERMISSION OF THE AUTHOR.  PLEASE READ THE LICENSE.

Usage: ringtonetools [ options ] <input filename> <output filename>
       -intype <filename type> [ imelody/rtttl/rtx/midi/kws/bmp/text/siemens ]
       -outtype <output type> [ wav/kws/mot/pdb/nokia/rtttl/samsung1/samsung2/siemens]
       -name <song name>
       -t <tempo [default: 140]>
   iMelody options:
       -a [force ringtonetools to ignore @'s in imelody's]
   Kyeocera options:
       -pause <number of quarter notes added [ default: 2  ]>
   Motorola options:
       -keypress [ Make keypress sequence for phones like v60t ]
   wav output options:
       -b <bits 8 or 16 for wav only [default: 16]>
       -f <sampling frequency for wav only [default: 44100]>
   logo options:
       -h <height> [ Height of Logo (default 14) ]
       -w <width> [ Width of Logo (default 72) ]
       -l <MCC> <MNC> [ Operator Logo (requires MCC and MNC) ]
       -m <message> Send a picture message
       -r [ reverse black n white ]
       -ss Send as screensaver
   nokia options:
       -x [ exclude //SCKL header ]
       -u [ only user-data-header (8bit) ]
       -k [ include user-data-header and //SCKL ]
       -s <sms size> [ Maximum size of SMS message (default 140)
       -transpose <pos or neg num > [ raise or lower song by n octaves ]
   midi options:
       -channel [ channel ]
       -track [ track ]


